eu_initiatives:
1. The Kiribati Local Government Association (KiLGA) was established under EU funding under its ARIAL Programme, which was aimed at setting up regional and national Local Government Associations in the Asia Caribbean and Pacific (ACP) countries; 
2. In September, 2017, KiLGA held a meeting with the European Union Pacific Office, based in Suva Fiji, to propose that the Association (KiLGA) be allowed to access the EU financial resources earmarked for CSO participation in the EU-Kiribati's Line and Phoenix Island Integrated Development Strategy 2016-2036; 
3. In February, 2018, KiLGA met an officer from the EU Pacific Office in Suva, who came to Kiribati, and agreed that the two should meet again in Suva in March, 2018, to discuss how KiLGA and the EU Pacific Office can work together to implement the Line and Phoenix Islands Integrated Development Strategy, particularly on components that deal with CSOs;
